p: The group-mean food consumption after weaning was comparable across all groups, including the control, in both sexes. There was a trend toward reduced food consumption in the mid-dose animals in both sexes, but differences did not reach statistical significance on most occasions ( Fig 4). In females of the low- and high dose groups, mean food consumption values were generally higher than that of the control, but again without statistical significance on most occasions ( Fig 4B).
